---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Extended Advanced Diploma — Year 1 of the PhD | Brenkley Doctoral College" description="The Extended Advanced Diploma is Year 1 of the Brenkley Doctoral College PhD — SCQF Level 11, 180 credits, with an embedded professional internship. A standalone qualification or the first step to a partner-university doctorate. £4,800 per year.">

  <section class="bg-surface border-b border-border py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <p class="section-label mb-4">Programme &mdash; Year 1 of the PhD</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Extended Advanced Diploma</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-accent font-medium mb-4">SCQF Level 11 &mdash; 180 Credits &mdash; Includes Applied Internship &mdash; £4,800 per year</p>
      <p class="text-lg text-muted max-w-2xl">The Extended Advanced Diploma is Year 1 of the Brenkley Doctoral College PhD — a substantive, credit-rated qualification for professionals who want to conduct supervised original research and put theory into practice through a structured internship. Credit-rated at SCQF Level 11 (180 credits), it is a recognised and respected standalone qualification, and also the foundation year for progression to a full doctorate with one of our partner universities.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-4 gap-6 mb-12">
        <div class="card text-center">
          <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-accent mb-2">18–24 Months</div>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted">Part-time, flexible scheduling</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card text-center">
          <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-accent mb-2">SCQF Level 11</div>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted">180 credits within the Scottish Credit and Qualifications Framework</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card text-center">
          <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-accent mb-2">Internship Included</div>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted">Applied placement putting research theory into professional practice</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card text-center">
          <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-accent mb-2">£4,800/yr</div>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted">Total £7,200–£9,600 depending on duration</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12">
        <div>
          <p class="section-label mb-3">About the Extended Advanced Diploma</p>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Research and Practice at the Highest Pre-Doctoral Level</h2>
          <p class="text-muted mb-4">The Extended Advanced Diploma is a research degree, not a taught postgraduate qualification. It requires you to design and conduct an original research project, submit a substantial thesis (typically 40,000–60,000 words), pass an oral examination, and complete a supervised internship applying your research theory to a live professional context. It is a meaningful intellectual achievement and a recognised academic qualification.</p>
          <p class="text-muted mb-4">Credit-rated at SCQF Level 11 (180 credits) — the level and credit weight of the first year of a Scottish doctoral degree — it enables recognition and potential credit transfer within the UK higher education system.</p>
          <p class="text-muted">Successful completion is recognised as Year 1 of the Brenkley Doctoral College PhD, with the option to progress to Years 2 and 3 at one of our partner universities, or to a DBA or EdD.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="section-label mb-3">Who Should Apply</p>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Is the Extended Advanced Diploma Right for You?</h2>
          <div class="space-y-3">
            <div class="card">
              <p class="text-muted text-sm">You want to conduct rigorous original research but are not ready to commit to three or more years of doctoral study.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card">
              <p class="text-muted text-sm">You want a recognised research qualification, backed by real-world applied experience, to advance your professional or academic career without a full doctorate.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card">
              <p class="text-muted text-sm">You are testing whether doctoral-level research is for you, with the option to progress to a full doctorate at a partner university if you wish.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card">
              <p class="text-muted text-sm">You have a specific, bounded research question that can be addressed in 18–24 months of part-time study, and want to put your findings into practice through an internship.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Structure -->
  <section class="bg-surface border-y border-border py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <p class="section-label mb-3">Programme Structure</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">18–24 Months to the Extended Advanced Diploma</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-bold mb-3 text-accent">Stage 1 (Months 1–9)</h3>
          <ul class="text-muted text-sm space-y-2">
            <li>Introduction to Research Methods module</li>
            <li>Literature review development</li>
            <li>Research design and ethics approval</li>
            <li>Research proposal submission and approval</li>
            <li>Supervision meetings (minimum 6 in first nine months)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-bold mb-3 text-accent">Stage 2 (Months 10–18/24)</h3>
          <ul class="text-muted text-sm space-y-2">
            <li>Data collection and analysis</li>
            <li>Thesis writing with supervisor feedback</li>
            <li>Progress review at month 12</li>
            <li>Thesis submission (40,000–60,000 words)</li>
            <li>Oral examination (viva voce)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-bold mb-3 text-accent">Applied Internship</h3>
          <ul class="text-muted text-sm space-y-2">
            <li>Structured placement in a professional or organisational setting</li>
            <li>Direct application of your research theory and findings to practice</li>
            <li>Supervised and assessed alongside your thesis work</li>
            <li>Internship outcomes report contributes to final credit award</li>
            <li>Award of the Extended Advanced Diploma (SCQF 11, 180 credits)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Progression -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <p class="section-label mb-3">Progression</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">Your Choice of Partner University for Years 2 and 3</h2>
      <p class="text-muted mb-8 max-w-3xl">The Extended Advanced Diploma stands on its own as a completed qualification. If you wish to continue to a full PhD, you choose which partner university you progress to for Years 2 and 3 — the research and thesis phases of the doctorate — rather than being assigned one.</p>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-3">Choice of Institution</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm">Brenkley Doctoral College maintains progression arrangements with a network of partner universities. You select the institution that best fits your research area, career goals, and circumstances.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-3">Subject to Admission</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm">Progression is via each university's own articulation process. Your Extended Advanced Diploma and Year 1 credits support your application, but acceptance is confirmed by the partner university's admissions process, not guaranteed automatically.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-3">No Obligation to Progress</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm">There is no requirement to continue. Many learners complete the Extended Advanced Diploma as a standalone qualification and career milestone in its own right.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Requirements -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <p class="section-label mb-3">Entry Requirements</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">What We Look For</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-3">Academic</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm">Bachelor's degree at 2:1 or above, or equivalent. A postgraduate qualification is not required, though applicants with a Master's degree are welcome. Strong professional portfolios are considered alongside academic qualifications.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-3">Professional</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm">Relevant professional experience is valued but not strictly required at the level demanded by our doctoral programmes. The Extended Advanced Diploma is appropriate for earlier-career professionals as well as senior practitioners, and your internship placement can draw on your existing sector or a new one.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-3">Research Statement</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm">A short research statement of 500–800 words outlining your proposed research area, its significance, and your initial thoughts on methodology. This is discussed and developed at interview.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-surface border-t border-border py-16 px-6 text-center">
    <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Start with Year 1 of the PhD</h2>
      <p class="text-muted mb-8">The Extended Advanced Diploma is a meaningful first step into research and practice. Apply today and begin the process of becoming a research-active professional — with a real qualification and an internship to show for it, whether or not you continue to the full doctorate.</p>
      <div class="flex gap-4 justify-center flex-wrap">
        <a href="/apply" class="btn-primary">Apply now</a>
        <a href="/connect" class="btn-outline">Speak to us</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
